🧠 HESTIA Command Reference

🚀 To Start Hestia

1. From terminal:
   python -m hearth.cli.hestia
2. VS Code Task Runner:
   Ctrl + Shift + P → Run Task → run hearth

🛑 To Exit Hestia
Use either of the following inside the Hestia prompt:
* `exit`
* `quit`

---

📝 To Make a Note
Inside Hestia:
log note [your message]


📘 To Get Digest (Reflections Summary)
* Daily digest:
  digest

* Weekly digest:
  weekly


📂 To Get Digest File Location (Outside Hestia)
From your terminal (outside Hestia):
python generate_digest.py
> ✅ This outputs the location of the stored reflection digest file.


💻 To Launch an App or Website

Inside Hestia:
launch [app name] [optional target or URL]

🧠 To Teach Hestia How to Launch Something

➤ For Desktop Applications:
teach launch [app name] path "[full/path/to/app.exe]"

➤ For Websites:
teach launch [app name] url "[website-url]"


➤ For UWP Apps via Shell:
teach launch [app name] shell [AppID]



📄 Show details of a known app:
show [app name]


📜 List all apps Hestia knows:
list apps


🧹 Forget an app:
forget [app name]


✏️ Rename a known app:
rename [old_name] to [new_name]

